items.title: U.S. and Iran say talks over Tehran's nuclear program make progress and set plans for more
items.description: Iran and the U.S. will begin having experts meet to discuss details of a possible deal over Tehran's rapidly advancing nuclear program.

items.title: Anti-Trump protesters turn out for rallies in New York, Washington, D.C., and other cities nationwide
items.description: Opponents of President Donald Trump's administration took to the streets to decry what they see as threats to the nation's democratic ideals.

items.title: U.S. Supreme Court temporarily blocks deportations of Venezuelan migrants under wartime law
items.description: The U.S. Supreme Court early on Saturday paused President Donald Trump's administration from deporting Venezuelan men in immigration custody.

items.title: White House claims letter to Harvard with demands was an 'unauthorized' mistake: NYT
items.description: The April 11 letter set off a public feud between the White House and Harvard University.

items.title: Trump to reclassify many federal workers, making them easier to fire
items.description: Trump to reclassify many federal workers, making them easier to fire.
